## DESIGN PRINCIPLES

- Segmentation by trust level
- Default deny between VLANs
- Centralized control and routing via OPNsense
- Servers isolated from clients
- IoT treated as untrusted
- Sandbox treated as hostile
- Switch handles segmentation; firewall handles policy (separation of concerns)

---

## SUMMARY

This topology represents a segmented home lab architecture with:

- Dedicated firewall (OPNsense)
- VLAN-based network segmentation across 6 zones
- Separate server, client, IoT, and management networks
- Centralized logging (Splunk) and identity services (Active Directory) — operational
- Isolated sandbox environment (planned)

The core network is in a stable, operational state. The environment will continue to evolve as monitoring/detection (Splunk dashboards, Sysmon, IDS/IPS), the sandbox zone, and firewall hardening are finalized.
